The paper deals with sparse reconstruction and support selection, which are common tasks in machine learning, computer vision, and signal processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on sparse vectors and linear combinations, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.SI.
